# Component and Page Rules

## Styling

- Use **Tailwind CSS classes only** — no inline `style` attributes
- Do not add custom CSS classes outside `src/assets/styles/tailwind.css`
- Dark mode variants must use `dark:` prefix, never hardcode colors for dark mode only
- Responsive breakpoints: `sm:` (640px), `md:` (768px), `lg:` (1024px), `xl:` (1280px)

## Component Architecture

- Components must accept data via props — never hardcode marketing copy inside `.astro` files
- Text content (headlines, descriptions, CTAs) must come from:
  - Props passed from the page
  - JSON files in `src/data/`
  - NOT hardcoded strings in component files
- Reference the canonical Astrowind widget pattern in `src/components/widgets/` for new sections

## Page Files

- Pages should be thin — they import components and pass data, no business logic
- Every `.astro` page must import and render `<RiskBanner />` before the closing `</Layout>` tag
- Page metadata (title, description) must be set via the `metadata` prop on `<Layout>`

## Compliance Component Rule

The following components in `src/components/compliance/` are protected:
- `RiskBanner.astro` — must never be removed or hidden via CSS

If you need to adjust styling of compliance components, ask the user first.

## New Page Checklist

When creating a new page, ensure:
1. `<Layout metadata={...}>` wrapper is present
2. `<RiskBanner />` is included
3. Page is added to `src/navigation.ts` if it should appear in nav or footer
4. Page has proper `metadata.title` and `metadata.description`
